FBIS3-55041 "drsov003_e_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-003 Document Type:Daily Report 5 Jan 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Envoy to UN on U.S., Russian Nuclear Stance LD0401212994 Kiev Ukrayinske Telebachennya Network in Ukrainian 1900 GMT 4 Jan 94 LD0401212994 Kiev Ukrayinske Telebachennya Network Language: Ukrainian Article Type:BFN [Text] Viktor Batyuk, our state's permanent representative at the United Nations, took part in a briefing at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs today. He noted in particular that Ukraine's delegation has done great work explaining Ukraine's foreign policy. Unfortunately, however, it is nevertheless impossible to surpass the activity of one delegation and the furious pressure on the part of the mass media and government structures of the United States and Russia, which are distorting our stance regarding nuclear weapons, said Viktor Batyuk.
